{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1467928846,"nonce":"sltu7PvEAydRXIgGGLRmsYEk9/A=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMTIyMDU1NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/836#issuecomment-231220554"},"message":"That's for the pointers @abretaud. I didn't get to look at it much, but I did confirm the problem comes from sourcing `env.sh` from the zlib package. Not sure why, but it interferes with samtools make process. I'm thinking your are probably right to avoid building at least samtools. Is there a \"standard\" way to apply patches in galaxy packages?","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1467993732,"nonce":"eJMYHU/AaQsSNZdWLeN+VXYTBOA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMTM5OTU5OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/836#issuecomment-231399599"},"message":"A bit more digging and it seems like having `C_INCLUDE_PATH` and `CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH` pointing to zlib 1.2.8 is causing the issue. If I unset those, samtools builds fine, and they are not set in the various `package_samtools_0_1_19` `tool_dependency.xml` files. So a couple of options:\n1. Remove the zlib path from `C_INLUDE_PATH` and `CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH` prior to building trinity-plugins. This avoids patching Makefiles, etc.\n2. Patch the Makefile to avoid building samtools and instead provide samtools as a galaxy dependency. The problem here is that the trinity tools already use samtools 1.2 as a dependency, yet trinity builds 0.1.19. Thus this could change behavior and/or break things if trinity is expecting 0.1.19.\n\n@abretaud @bgruening Comments, suggestions?","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1467994518,"nonce":"vxWI0IC8W+8RvLoo2soTW06YMsw=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzMTQwMjg1MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/836#issuecomment-231402851"},"message":"Hmmm... Actually, looking at this now, it's not clear that `package_trinity_2_1_1` ever actually uses the built samtools 0.1.19. There is no directive to move `trinity-plugins/samtools` and the path is never set for that subdirectory either. Perhaps simply avoiding building samtools will work?","files":null}]}